{
  "texts": [
    "The LILA dataset evaluates LLMs' mathematical reasoning skills through 23 tasks across four dimensions.",
    "It scrutinizes fundamental mathematical skills, algebra, probability theory, calculus, and other pertinent mathematical knowledge.",
    "These four dimensions encompass mathematical proficiency, language format, language diversity, and external knowledge.",
    "• MiniF2F v1 (Zheng et al, 2022).",
    "The MiniF2F v1 dataset consists of 488 statements presenting Olympiad-level mathematical problems, aiming to evaluate the neural mathematical reasoning capabilities."
  ]
}